# QSerialTerminal
A serial monitor in C++ using the Qt5 framework, similar to the official Arduino IDE serial monitor 

To install (Linux): 

Open up a terminal shell and clone the source:  
    git clone https://github.com/tlewiscpp/QSerialTerminal

Run one of the two scripts with the target installation directory as an argument (the directory will be created if it does not exist):
	./install-cmake.sh ~/QSerialTerminalBuild/
	or
	./install-qmake.sh ~/QSerialTerminalBuild/

To build and install (Windows):
Install Tortoisegit and Qt. See DEVEL-WINDOWS.txt for details
